<h1>Starboard</h1>

The Starboard allows Server Members to react with a ‚≠ê on a message, and have it
sent to a special channel automatically with the message content, image
attached, or if it's an embed it sends the embed's fields

</br> </br>

<h3>Setup</h3>
Configurating the starboard is done through the <code><a href="/commands/Configuration/starboard" ><%= prefix %>starboard</a></code> command, and it's subcommands.

<ol>
    <li>Create a channel that you want starred message to be sent into, preferably public for all to see.</li>
    <li>Set the Starboard Channel with <code><%= prefix %>starboard channel &lt;value&gt;</code>, this will be the channel that all starred messages will be sent to.</li>
    <li>Enable the Starboard with <code><%= prefix %>starboard enable</code>, this will enable messages being sent into the channel that you previously set when a message is starred</li>
</ol>
Have Fun!

</br> </br> A quick overview of all subcommands below. </br> </br>
<h5>Subcommands</h5>
<ul>
	<li><code>enable</code> Enables the Starboard</li>
	<li><code>disable</code> Disables the Starboard</li>
	<li><code>channel &lt;value&gt;</code> Set the role that all starred messages will be sent into</li>
</ul>

